                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-586" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-586" type="surname" value="HILL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370130-name-586" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE HILL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a shoemaker, residing at Edmonton. The pri<lb></lb>soner was brought to me by a man in distress, and I gave him work—he re<lb></lb>maned with me about eight weeks, and lived in the house with us—when I got up, on the morning of the 25th of January, I misted this property from the front room—the prisoner was gone when I got up—I got on a coach and overtook him at Kingsland, in a cart, with the property.</p>
